210.1262.  Notification, filing, contents. — The notification shall be filed by the director or his or her designee of the residential care facility to the department on forms provided by the department and shall contain the following information:
  (1)  Name, street address, mailing address, and phone number of the residential care facility;
  (2)  Name of the director, owner, operator, all staff members, volunteers, and any individual eighteen years of age or older who resides at or on the property of the residential care facility;
  (3)  Name and description of the agency or organization operating the residential care facility, including a statement as to whether the agency or organization is incorporated;
  (4)  Name and address of the sponsoring organization of the residential care facility, if applicable;
  (5)  School or schools attended by the children served by the residential care facility;
  (6)  Fire and safety inspection certificate;
  (7)  Local health department inspection certificate; and
  (8)  Proof that medical records are maintained for each child.
(L. 2021 H.B. 557 & 560) 
Effective 7-14-21
